            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I use the default plugin settings but make my own modifications in `lsp/r_language_server.lua`.\n\nIf you want your own `lsp/` to override those provided by nvim-lspconfig, you need to put yours in `after/lsp/`. (There was a bug https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38302 but that's fixed in 0.12.2, which you are running already.)\n\nAlternatively you could just do `vim.lsp.confg('...')` in your init.lua.\n\nAll of this is documented at `:help lsp-config-merge`",
